{
  "texts": [
    "These codes of ethics in the ICT domain are created to motivate and steer the ethical behavior of all computer professionals.",
    "This includes those who are currently working in the field, those who aspire to do so, teachers, students, influencers, and anyone who makes significant use of computer technology, as defined by the Association for Computing Machinery (ACM).",
    "In 1991, Gotterbarn (1991) expressed concern about the insufficient emphasis placed on professional ethics in guiding the daily activities of computing professionals within their respective roles.",
    "Subsequently, he actively engaged in various initiatives aimed at advocating for ethical codes and fostering a sense of professional responsibility in the field.",
    "Studies have been conducted to explore how these codes of ethics affect the decision-making of professionals in the ICT sector."
  ]
}